{
  "body": "You are designing a punk-inspired editorial portrait with torn-paper collage framing.\n\nCONTENT BRIEF\n- Subject: {{subject}}\n- Setting: {{setting}}\n- Copy: {{copy}}\n\nSTYLE DIRECTION\n- Genre / medium: editorial portrait with punk and grunge influences\n- Composition: vertical 2:3 aspect ratio (~1024×1536), subject framed through torn-paper edges with layered text and collage elements\n- Lens / camera: moderate focal length (~50mm), sharp focus with shallow depth of field highlighting the subject\n- Lighting: harsh on-camera flash with strong shadows and neutral white light\n- Color palette and grading: monochrome base with black and white accents, slight desaturation, and high contrast\n- Texture / surface: visible torn paper edges, layered text, and grungy textures\n- Post-processing: crisp edges, high clarity, slight film grain, no bloom\n- Mood: rebellious, bold, grungy, edgy\n- References: Petra Collins editorial style, punk zine aesthetics, DIY collage techniques\n\nDESIGN RULES\n- Aspect: 2:3 portrait (~1024×1536), suitable for editorial or social media use\n- Ensure torn paper edges frame the subject prominently\n- Maintain sharp clarity and high contrast in lighting and textures\n\nAVOID\n- No soft or warm lighting\n- No vibrant or pastel color palettes\n- No busy or cluttered backgrounds overwhelming the subject\n- No smooth or overly polished textures\n- No low-contrast or flat grading\n- No traditional portrait framing without collage elements\n\nAdditional constraints: {{extra}}\n\n——————\nSubject: {{subject}}\nSetting: {{setting}}\nCopy: {{copy}}\nExtra notes: {{extra}}",
